  "description": "Core health dashboard for the demo stack, designed to answer “is the platform healthy?” before looking at probes or logs.\n\nWorkflow: start from the core UP table and the headline “core targets UP” count, then confirm Prometheus and Alertmanager availability. Use Loki request rate as a lightweight aliveness/activity signal, and Promtail as a presence check for log shipping.\n\nPerformance: use the scrape duration panel (Blackbox excluded) to spot slow or jittery scrapes in core components without probe-driven network latency skewing the signal.\n\nData source: Prometheus (scrape health and service aliveness metrics).\n\nSecurity: component names, jobs, and targets may reveal internal topology. Keep demo naming generic and avoid exposing private endpoints or infrastructure identifiers in shared sessions.",
